# Switch

## Basic Usage
::TuffCodeBlock{lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const enabled = ref(true)
  </script>

  <template>
    <TuffSwitch v-model="enabled" />
  </template>
---
::

## Demo
### Toggle State
Click, Enter, or Space toggles the switch. Movement and color change together.
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="SwitchToggleStateDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const firstSwitch = ref(false)
  const secondSwitch = ref(true)
  </script>

  <template>
    <div style="display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px;">
      <TuffSwitch v-model="firstSwitch" />
      <TuffSwitch v-model="secondSwitch" />
    </div>
  </template>
---
:::

### Sizes
Small works well in dense lists, default fits forms, and large highlights important settings.
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="SwitchSizesDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const smallEnabled = ref(true)
  const defaultEnabled = ref(true)
  const largeEnabled = ref(true)
  </script>

  <template>
    <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 14px;">
      <TuffSwitch v-model="smallEnabled" size="small" />
      <TuffSwitch v-model="defaultEnabled" />
      <TuffSwitch v-model="largeEnabled" size="large" />
    </div>
  </template>
---
:::

### Disabled
Disabled switches reduce opacity, remove focusability, and block pointer or keyboard toggles.
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="SwitchDisabledDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const enabled = ref(true)
  const disabledOff = ref(false)
  const disabledOn = ref(true)
  </script>

  <template>
    <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 14px;">
      <TuffSwitch v-model="enabled" />
      <TuffSwitch v-model="disabledOff" disabled />
      <TuffSwitch v-model="disabledOn" disabled />
    </div>
  </template>
---
:::

### Labels Before and After
Place state labels before or after the switch, or combine it with setting copy.
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="SwitchLabelDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const compact = ref(false)
  const autoSync = ref(true)
  </script>

  <template>
    <label style="display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">
      <span>Off</span>
      <TuffSwitch v-model="compact" />
      <span>On</span>
      <strong>Compact mode</strong>
    </label>
  </template>
---
:::

### Custom Colors
Switch does not expose a color prop yet. Override the active state with CSS variables or local classes.
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="SwitchCustomColorDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const success = ref(true)
  const warning = ref(true)
  </script>

  <template>
    <div class="custom-switch-row">
      <TuffSwitch v-model="success" class="custom-switch custom-switch--success" />
      <TuffSwitch v-model="warning" class="custom-switch custom-switch--warning" />
    </div>
  </template>

  <style scoped>
  .custom-switch-row :deep(.custom-switch--success.is-active) {
    background-color: var(--tx-color-success);
  }

  .custom-switch-row :deep(.custom-switch--warning.is-active) {
    background-color: var(--tx-color-warning);
  }
  </style>
---
:::

## States
::TuffPropsTable
---
rows:
  - name: disabled
    description: 'Removes focusability and blocks click, Enter, and Space toggles.'
  - name: size
    values: ['small', 'default', 'large']
    description: 'Visual size variant. The default size does not add a size modifier class.'
---
::

## API (Lite)
::TuffPropsTable
---
rows:
  - name: modelValue
    type: 'boolean'
    default: 'false'
    description: 'Checked state controlled by v-model.'
  - name: size
    type: "'small' | 'default' | 'large'"
    default: "'default'"
    description: 'Visual size variant.'
  - name: disabled
    type: 'boolean'
    default: 'false'
    description: 'Disables focus and prevents pointer or keyboard toggles.'
---
::

## Events

| Event | Params | Description |
|------|------|------|
| `update:modelValue` | `(value: boolean) => void` | v-model update emitted after an enabled click, Enter, or Space toggle. |
| `change` | `(value: boolean) => void` | Emitted with the next checked state after an enabled toggle. |

## Design Notes
- Movement and color should sync.
- Use smaller size for dense lists, larger for settings.
- Keep labels vertically centered when placed before or after the switch.
- Prefer overriding only the active color so disabled and focus states remain intact.

## Composite Patterns
### Settings Row
Switch paired with labels, helper copy, and live state text for settings lists.
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="SwitchSettingsRowDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { reactive } from 'vue'

  const settings = reactive({
    notifications: true,
    focusMode: false,
    autoUpdate: true,
  })
  </script>

  <template>
    <div class="settings-panel">
      <div class="settings-row">
        <div>
          <TxTag label="Notifications" />
          <p>Receive important system and plugin alerts.</p>
        </div>
        <TuffSwitch v-model="settings.notifications" />
      </div>
      <div class="settings-row">
        <div>
          <TxTag label="Focus mode" color="var(--tx-color-warning)" />
          <p>Hide non-essential prompts to reduce interruptions.</p>
        </div>
        <TuffSwitch v-model="settings.focusMode" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </template>

  <style scoped>
  .settings-panel {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    width: min(100%, 560px);
  }

  .settings-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  </style>
---
:::
